				{
					"role": "title",
					"layout": "titleLayout",
					"text": "What This Couple Found Inside a 50-Year-Old Safe Hidden Behind Their Wall Is Straight Out of a Movie",
					"textStyle": "titleStyle"
				},
				{
					"role": "intro",
					"layout": "introLayout",
					"text": "See, it totally pays to DIY. Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Maecenas pellentesque libero a erat dapibus volutpat. Vestibulum varius.",
					"textStyle": "introStyle",
					"format": "markdown"
				},
				{
					"role": "divider",
					"stroke": {
						"color": "#FFF0"
					},
					"layout": "blackStrokeLayout1",
					"style": "baseStrokeStyle"
				},
				{
					"role": "author",
					"layout": "authorLayout",
					"text": "By Brie Schwartz",
					"textStyle": "authorStyle"
				},
				{
					"role": "divider",
					"stroke": {
						"color": "#FFF0"
					},
					"layout": "blackStrokeLayout2",
					"style": "baseStrokeStyle"
				},
				{ 
					 "role": "medium_rectangle_advertisement",
					 "layout": "adLayout",
					 "bannerType": "standard"
				},
				{
					"role": "body",
					"text": "A Phoenix couple kicking off some home renovations were shocked to find that inside their walls instead of rusty pipes or creepy crawlers, there was a 50-year-old safe, just waiting to be cracked.",
					"layout": "bodyLayout",
					"textStyle": "bodyStyleFirst",
					"format": "markdown"
				},
				{
					"role": "body",
					"text": "When they first moved into their home, which the couple, who posted their incredible story on [Imgur](http://imgur.com/gallery/ldW7B) describe as a \"fixer upper,\" they found a safe code in the back of a medicine cabinet but never knew where it led.",
					"layout": "bodyLayout",
					"textStyle": "bodyStyle",
					"format": "markdown"
				},
				{
					"role": "body",
					"text": "Once they tore down their kitchen island and started hammering away, they found the [mystery](http://www.womansday.com/relationships/family-friends/news/a51541/woman-finds-decades-old-mystery-letter-hidden-inside-picture-frame/) box.",
					"layout": "bodyLayout",
					"textStyle": "bodyStyle",
					"format": "markdown"
				},
				{
					"role": "heading1",
					"layout": "heading1Layout",
					"text": "Opening the \"Mystery Box\"",
					"textStyle": "heading1Style",
					"format": "markdown"
				},
				{
					"role": "body",
					"text": "Using the code that they luckily secreted away, they were able to get the safe open after a dozen attempts. And what did they find inside? $51,080, mostly in $100 notes and a bottle of bourbon dated 1960.",
					"layout": "bodyLayout",
					"textStyle": "bodyStyle",
					"format": "markdown"
				},
				{
					"role": "body",
					"text": "\"We stared in disbelief. Time stood still. I started to reach in the safe and Eddie yelled, 'Wait it might be booby trapped!' I'm still laughing at that one,\" the woman writes on Imgur. Yet, nothing would stop her from having at that bourbon.",
					"layout": "bodyLayout",
					"textStyle": "bodyStyle",
					"format": "markdown"
				},
				{
					"role": "divider",
					"stroke": {
						"color": "#FFF0"
					},
					"layout": "blackStrokeLayout3",
					"style": "baseStrokeStyle"
				},
				{
					"role": "pullquote",
					"layout": "pullQuoteLayout",
					"text": "\u201CI started to reach in the safe and Eddie yelled, 'Wait it might be booby trapped!' I'm still laughing at that one...\u201D",
					"textStyle": "pullQuoteStyle",
					"format": "markdown"
				},
				{
					"role": "divider",
					"stroke": {
						"color": "#FFF0"
					},
					"layout": "blackStrokeLayout4",
					"style": "baseStrokeStyle"
				},
				{
					"role": "body",
					"text": "Besides the cash and the hooch, the safe also contained\u2014and this is where it gets interesting\u2014a book called _A Guide for the Perplexed_, published in 1977, that appears to contain clues. Inside, there was a black and white photo of a mystery (and, might we add, dapper) man. On the back of Mr. Handsome's pic, there was a note that reads:",
					"layout": "bodyLayout",
					"textStyle": "bodyStyle",
					"format": "markdown"
				},
				{
					"role": "quote",
					"text": "Alan, I have a book you must read. I've underlined a few key passages. Your friend, Vincent",
					"layout": "blockQuoteLayout",
					"textStyle": "blockQuoteStyle",
					"style": "blockQuoteContainerStyle",
					"format": "markdown"
				},
				{
					"role": "body",
					"text": "There was one more poignant passage Vincent thoughtfully pointed out to Alan: \"Most Modern Readers will be reluctant to believe that perfect happiness is attainable by methods of which their modern world knows nothing.\" Was this, perhaps the 1977 equivalent of saying, 'stop coveting that iWatch and find joy in simple walks and stuff? Unclear, but it certainly gives you pause.",
					"layout": "bodyLayout",
					"textStyle": "bodyStyle",
					"format": "markdown"
				},
				{
					"role": "body",
					"text": "_**UPDATE, 8/29:** Well, we thought it sounded too good to be true, and in fact, it was. The couple whose treasure hunt story took the Internet by storm this week have fessed up: They fabricated the whole thing. The Chive has more details on how they pulled off to the ruse. And while we feel chagrined, we're happy to see the money they \"discovered\" has found a good home: They donated it to a local no-kill animal shelter._",
					"layout": "bodyLayout",
					"textStyle": "bodyStyle",
					"format": "markdown"
				},
				{
					"role": "banner_advertisement",
					"bannerType": "standard"
				}
			]
		}
